# Consumer Loan Agreement (TILA)

Produce a closed-end consumer loan agreement with a compliant TILA disclosure box and enforceable loan terms.

## Prerequisites

1. **Parties** — legal names, entity types, addresses, and authorized signers for lender and all borrowers/co-borrowers.
2. **Loan economics** — principal, interest rate, term, payment frequency, first payment date, fees, and any prepaid finance charges.
3. **Security** — collateral description or confirmation the loan is unsecured; required insurance details if secured.
4. **State law** — jurisdiction, caps on late fees/prepayment penalties, notice-to-cure requirements, and any mandated notices.
5. **Regulatory scope** — confirm closed-end, consumer-purpose credit and whether any special rules apply (mortgage, high-cost, military, etc.).

## Output Structure / Process

**Section Order (strict):**

| Order | Section | Required Content |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | TILA Disclosure Box | Conspicuous “FEDERAL TRUTH IN LENDING DISCLOSURES” heading; labeled items; clear segregation; placed before other terms. |
| 2 | Loan Terms | Promise to pay; purpose statement (consumer purpose); term; payment timing; payment method. |
| 3 | Prepayment / Late Fees | Right to prepay; penalty terms if any; grace period and late charge formula. |
| 4 | Security / Collateral | Security interest grant, collateral description, perfection and maintenance covenants. |
| 5 | Default / Acceleration | Events of default; notice-to-cure; acceleration; remedies. |
| 6 | Insurance / Advances | Required insurance; loss payee; lender advances and repayment. |
| 7 | Payment Application | Application order of payments. |
| 8 | Notices / Regulatory | Co-signer notice (if applicable); SCRA notice (if applicable); state-required notices. |
| 9 | Execution | Receipt acknowledgement; signatures for borrowers, co-signers, and lender. |

**Disclosure Box Template (place on page 1):**
```text
FEDERAL TRUTH IN LENDING DISCLOSURES

Lender: [Legal Name] [DBA if any]
Address: [Street, City, State, ZIP]
Contact: [Phone/Email]

Borrower(s): [Full Legal Name(s)]
Address: [Street, City, State, ZIP]

Amount Financed (The amount of credit provided to you or on your behalf): $[Amount]
Finance Charge (The dollar amount the credit will cost you): $[Amount]
Annual Percentage Rate (The cost of your credit as a yearly rate): [APR]%
Total of Payments (The amount you will have paid after you have made all payments as scheduled): $[Amount]

Payment Schedule (Your payment schedule will be):
[Either]
[ ] [Number] payments of $[Amount] due [frequency], beginning [date]
[Or]
See schedule below:
```

**Payment Schedule (use if non-uniform or balloon):**
```text
Payment # | Due Date | Amount
1 | [Date] | $[Amount]
2 | [Date] | $[Amount]
...
N | [Date] | $[Amount]
```

**Calculation Checklist (must be completed before drafting):**
- [ ] Amount Financed = principal minus prepaid finance charges plus any financed fees.
- [ ] Finance Charge includes all charges imposed as a condition of credit.
- [ ] APR calculated per Regulation Z methodology; accuracy within Reg Z tolerances [VERIFY].
- [ ] Total of Payments = Amount Financed + Finance Charge.
- [ ] Payment schedule totals match Total of Payments.

**Key Clause Templates (insert and tailor):**

**Prepayment (no penalty):**
```text
You may prepay the unpaid principal at any time, in whole or in part, without penalty. If you prepay in full, you will not receive a refund of any finance charge except as required by law, and any refund will be calculated using the actuarial method.
```

**Late Charge:**
```text
If we do not receive any payment within [X] days after its due date, you will pay a late charge of [Y]% of the unpaid portion of the scheduled payment (or $[Z], whichever is less). One late charge applies per late payment and is not compounded.
```

**Security Interest (secured loan):**
```text
You grant us a security interest in the collateral described below. You will keep it insured, in good condition, and free of other liens, and you will not sell or transfer it without our written consent.
Collateral: [Full description, serial/VIN, legal description for real property]
```

**Unsecured Statement (if applicable):**
```text
This is an unsecured loan. You are not providing collateral to secure this obligation.
```

**Default / Acceleration:**
```text
Events of default include failure to pay, breach of this Agreement, insolvency or bankruptcy, material misrepresentation, or failure to maintain required insurance. Subject to any required notice and cure period, we may declare the unpaid balance immediately due and pursue all lawful remedies.

